==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bordar
<hw>Bord"ar</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>bordarius</ets>, fr. <ets>borda</ets> a cottage; of uncertain
origin.]</ety> <def>A villein who rendered menial service for his
cottage; a cottier.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The cottar, the <qex>bordar</qex>, and the laborer were bound to
aid in the work of the home farm.</q> <rj><qau>J. R.
Green.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bordeaux</ent>⟦br⟧
